added.title: Total Jeopardy!
added.description: This is Jeopardy! In fact, this is a very special episode of Jeopardy for two reasons. First, Velma and Shaggy are contestants. And second, they're competing against Andy the Brain Bot (a semi-sentient super-smart robot), who's standing at the lecterns with them. Scooby and our gang of mystery solvers are super excited to meet famous TV personality and gameshow host Alex Trebek! But, it's lucky our heroes are on hand because when Velma and Shaggy start outscoring the Brain Bot, it causes the robot to go a little crazy. It threatens to destroy everything if it can't manage to win. Our gang and Mr. Trebek must get to the bottom of who's really behind this robot's dangerous actions, or when they say Final Jeopardy, they really mean it!

added.title: Scooby-Doo and the Sky Town Cool School!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang arrive at a mountaintop cool school run by none other than famous actor Billy Dee Williams. They're here to learn how to be cool, and Mr. Williams is the smooth-tongued professor of suave. But, the gang loses their cool when an angry pterodactyl monster keeps attacking them and the school trying to scare everyone away. But, Billy Dee has extra cool to spare, and he and the gang work together to get to the bottom of this kooky mystery before it's too late.

added.title: Falling Star Man!
added.description: Driving outside Shreveport, Louisiana, our gang of mystery solvers is run off the road by a shooting star that crashes down in the middle of the large ranch belonging to none-other than famous football hall of famer and TV sports host, Terry Bradshaw! Upon further investigation, the "shooting star" turns out to be a spaceship unleashing an alien monster on the local countryside! The gang and Mr. Bradshaw work together to get to the bottom of this space alien mystery and figure out what this alien is really after: championship rings or giant donuts.

added.title: Dark Diner of Route 66!
added.description: Scooby and Shaggy meet up with their biker buddy, Axl Rose, on a tour of famous roadside diners along iconic Route 66. The diner they're heading for is famous for its varieties of delicious pies. But soon, they all find themselves embroiled in a crazy mystery involving spooky mudmen, the lost ruins of an ancient civilization and a treasure of Spanish gold.

added.title: A Haunt of a Thousand Voices!
added.description: When Daphne takes the rest of the gang to meet her friend, famous voice over actor Frank Welker, they inadvertently find themselves in the middle of a very strange mystery full of several different monsters and several different actors! The gang meets voice over actors Frank Welker, Grey DeLisle-Griffin, Matthew Lillard and Kate Micucci, who have all gathered to do their job of recording an episode of a hit animated show that vaguely seems to be about four teenagers and their talking animal. But, when different monsters show up and start abducting various actors from the group, it looks like our gang has a real mystery on their hands, even more mysterious than how the actors' voices all sound strangely familiar to our gang.

added.title: Scooby-Doo, Dog Wonder!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang are on the case of a Medusa Monster that's stealing priceless vases from millionaire art collectors, like Radley Crown and his beloved mutt. What they don't understand is that Radley Crown and his dog are none other than the Blue Falcon and his dog wonder, Dynomutt (who are setting a trap for the Medusa Monster themselves). When our gang's interference causes the Blue Falcon to be taken by the monster, it's up to Dynomutt to put on his Blue Falcon hat and be the brains of the operation. But, he'll need a new Dog Wonder and he picks Scooby-Doo for the job!

added.title: Splash Zone
added.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

added.title: Play Day
added.description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

added.title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
added.description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

added.title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
added.description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

added.title: A New View for Thomas
added.description: When Thomas spends the day carrying rockstar idol Harold across Sodor, he gains a new perspective on just how amazing it is to be his engine-self.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Skiff Sails Sodor
added.description: When Skiff gets a crack in his hull, Thomas needs to move him overland to Harwick for repairs, but Skiff's land-sickness makes that challenging.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Spiderweb
added.description: A gorgeous spider web in the park has Blippi wondering "How do spiders make their webs?" He sets off to find the answer! A very talented spider explains the artistic process and Blippi is surprised by the masterful picture that ends up in the spiders' web!

added.title: Sneeze
added.description: What is making Blippi sneeze? What makes anyone sneeze? Blippi shrinks down and flies up a nose to find out! A very mischievous piece of pollen demonstrates how to make a sneeze happen, resulting in Blippi himself getting blown away by a giant sneeze!

added.title: Please and Thank You Song
added.description: Mei goes around the farm with food for the animals. She offers them some food and the animals say "yes please"

added.title: Baa Baa Black Sheep
added.description: It's getting chilly on the farm! Summers dwindled into autumn and everyone is in need of some winter clothing

removed.title: Rock On
removed.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac and Tosh Gopher to build them a home underground. Daffy can't remove rocks from the area fast enough and fails to ask for help.

removed.title: Thomas' Promise
removed.description: When Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the same load to Whiff's Recycling Plant, Thomas suggests they each take half of the load, but Diesel turns it into a race.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Buzz In
removed.description: Bizzy Buzzard's mom hires The Looney Builders to build her family a new nest. Bizzy wants to help but keeps getting in the way creating all sorts of problems for the crew.

removed.title: Song of Sodor
removed.description: When Nia suggests adding a song to spice up Sir Topham Hatt's new bench unveiling, he calls upon her to write a song for the ceremony, but Nia soon finds she may have bitten off more than she can sing.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Ducks
removed.description: Blippi gets up close and personal with Declan the Duck in his quest to find how ducks float! Under the water, above the water, through feather tunnels and tooting air bubbles, Blippi and Declan work together to discover the answer.

removed.title: Birds Nest
removed.description: A storm has destroyed Jodie the Blue Jays bird nest! Good thing Blippi and FETCH are there to help. While FETCH is on egg-sitting duty, Jodie and Blippi go on a heist mission to acquire the materials needed to rebuild. It's never an impossible mission when friends work together!

removed.title: Splash Song
removed.description: Ella is drawing a bus when she lets her imagination runs wild!

removed.title: Recycle Stomp
removed.description: Mei, the children and some animals are in the park collecting trash to recycle!

removed.title: The Need for Feed/The Zipline Sisters of Treetop Woods
removed.description: MacBarm is bringing food to his hungry chickens, that is, until all of the food falls out of his truck./Grandma and her twin sister want to recreate their old zipline act, but quickly discover that the zipline no longer exists!

removed.title: That's the Way the Windmill Blows!/Mecha Machine Makers!
removed.description: The windmill isn't turning, which means Sunny Field Farm has no power. The windmill needs to turn again so Zee can launch his rocket!/Izzy and Timmy are making a bird caller for Grandma, but have trouble connecting pieces of their machine.
